{"node_id": "377cd9936b27514ca0d508b124947965", "title": "Create equivalent expressions by factoring", "description": "Use the distributive property to factor out common numerical factors from expressions with variables. Remember, the greatest common factor is not always the only common factor.", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Math", "Pre-algebra", "Variables & expressions", "Distributive property with variables", "Create equivalent expressions by factoring"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "e78a0c7632955856adfe6ddba837737e", "question_content": "**Factor $24j-16$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $24j-16$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $8$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}24j-16\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left( \\dfrac{24j-16}{8}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left( \\dfrac{24j}{8}-\\dfrac{16}{8}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=8(3j-2)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $24j-16$ is equivalent to $8(3j-2)$.", "####Factoring out $6$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}24j-16\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left( \\dfrac{24j-16}{6}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left( \\dfrac{24j}{6}-\\dfrac{16}{6}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left(4j-\\dfrac{8}{3}\\right)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $24j-16$ is *not* equivalent to $6(4j-2j)$.", "####Factoring out $4$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}24j-16\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left( \\dfrac{24j-16}{4}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left( \\dfrac{24j}{4}-\\dfrac{16}{4}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=4(6j-4)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $24j-16$ is equivalent to $4(6j-4)$.", "####Factoring out $2$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}24j-16\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left( \\dfrac{24j-16}{2}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left( \\dfrac{24j}{2}-\\dfrac{16}{2}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=2(12j-8)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $24j-16$ is *not* equivalent to $2(12-8)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $24j-16$:\n\n- $8(3j-2)$\n- $4(6j-4)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$8(3j-2)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$6(4j-2j)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$4(6j-4)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$2(12-8)$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "352b75fdaf01570b929205eb75ecf34a", "question_content": "**Factor $16a+72$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $16a+72$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $4$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}16a+72\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{16a+72}{4}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{16a}{4}+\\dfrac{72}{4}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=4(4a+18)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $16a+72$ is equivalent to $4(4a+18)$.", "####Factoring out $8$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}16a+72\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left(\\dfrac{16a+72}{8}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left(\\dfrac{16a}{8}+\\dfrac{72}{8}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=8(2a+9)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $16a+72$ is equivalent to $8(2a+9)$.", "####Factoring out $2$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}16a+72\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{16a+72}{2}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{16a}{2}+\\dfrac{72}{2}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=2(8a+36)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $16a+72$ is *not* equivalent to $2(8+36a)$ or to $2(8a+72)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $16a+72$:\n\n- $4(4a+18)$\n- $8(2a+9)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$4(4a+18)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$8(2a+9)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$2(8+36a)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$2(8a+72)$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "f8f8467ba69356728651aea983e857bd", "question_content": "**Factor $64b-16c$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $64b-16c$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $16$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}64b-16c\\\\\\\\\n&=16\\left(\\dfrac{64b-16c}{16}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=16\\left(\\dfrac{64b}{16}-\\dfrac{16c}{16}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=16(4b-c)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $64b-16c$ is equivalent to $16(4b-c)$.", "####Factoring out $4$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}64b-16c\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{64b-16c}{4}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{64b}{4}-\\dfrac{16c}{4}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=4(16b-4c)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $64b-16c$ is *not* equivalent to $4(16b-4)$.", "####Factoring out $8$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}64b-16c\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left(\\dfrac{64b-16c}{8}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left(\\dfrac{64b}{8}-\\dfrac{16c}{8}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=8(8b-2c)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $64b-16c$ is *not* equivalent to $8(8b+2c)$.", "####Factoring out $2$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}64b-16c\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{64b-16c}{2}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{64b}{2}-\\dfrac{16c}{2}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=2(32b-8c)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $64b-16c$ is equivalent to $2(32b-8c)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $64b-16c$:\n\n- $16(4b-c)$\n- $2(32b-8c)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$16(4b-c)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$4(16b-4)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$8(8b+2c)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$2(32b-8c)$", "correct": true}]}}}, {"item_id": "836d6c6191f3596b97e41d85a75ddeec", "question_content": "**Factor $48-8x$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $48-8x$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $3$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48-8x\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{48-8x}{3}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{48}{3}-\\dfrac{8x}{3}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(16-\\dfrac{8}{3}x\\right)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $48-8x$ is *not* equivalent to $3(16-8x)$.", "####Factoring out $2$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48-8x\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{48-8x}{2}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{48}{2}-\\dfrac{8x}{2}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=2(24-4x)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $48-8x$ is equivalent to $2(24-4x)$.", "####Factoring out $8$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48-8x\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left(\\dfrac{48-8x}{8}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=8\\left(\\dfrac{48}{8}-\\dfrac{8x}{8}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=8(6-x)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $48-8x$ is equivalent to $8(6-x)$.", "####Factoring out $4$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48-8x\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{48-8x}{4}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{48}{4}-\\dfrac{8x}{4}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=4(12-2x)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $48-8x$ is *not* equivalent to $4(12-4x)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $48-8x$:\n\n- $2(24-4x)$\n- $8(6-x)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$3(16-8x)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$2(24-4x)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$8(6-x)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$4(12-4x)$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "17eaf9b125385a509f7b4b017ee7cbd5", "question_content": "**Factor $72y+108z$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $72y+108z$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $9$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}72y+108z\\\\\\\\\n&=9\\left(\\dfrac{72y+108z}{9}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=9\\left(\\dfrac{72y}{9}+\\dfrac{108z}{9}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=9(8y+12z)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $72y+108z$ is *not* equivalent to $9(7y+12z)$.", "####Factoring out $36$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}72y+108z\\\\\\\\\n&=36\\left(\\dfrac{72y+108z}{36}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=36\\left(\\dfrac{72y}{36}+\\dfrac{108z}{36}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=36(2y+3z)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $72y+108z$ is equivalent to $36(2y+3z)$.", "####Factoring out $6$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}72y+108z\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left(\\dfrac{72y+108z}{6}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left(\\dfrac{72y}{6}+\\dfrac{108z}{6}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=6(12y+18z)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $72y+108z$ is *not* equivalent to $6(18y+12z)$.", "####Factoring out $12$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}72y+108z\\\\\\\\\n&=12\\left(\\dfrac{72y+108z}{12}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=12\\left(\\dfrac{72y}{12}+\\dfrac{108z}{12}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=12(6y+9z)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $72y+108z$ is equivalent to $12(6y+9z)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $72y+108z$:\n\n- $36(2y+3z)$\n- $12(6y+9z)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$9(7y+12z)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$36(2y+3z)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$6(18y+12z)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$12(6y+9z)$", "correct": true}]}}}, {"item_id": "5306c53240a35dd78f0baf297bdbe704", "question_content": "**Factor $18p-36$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $18p-36$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $3$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}18p-36\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{18p-36}{3}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{18p}{3}-\\dfrac{36}{3}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=3(6p-12)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $18p-36$ is *not* equivalent to $3(9p-12)$.", "####Factoring out $9$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}18p-36\\\\\\\\\n&=9\\left(\\dfrac{18p-36}{9}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=9\\left(\\dfrac{18p}{9}-\\dfrac{36}{9}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=9(2p-4)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $18p-36$ is *not* equivalent to $9(2p-4p)$.", "####Factoring out $2$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}18p-36\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{18p-36}{2}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{18p}{2}-\\dfrac{36}{2}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=2(9p-18)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $18p-36$ is equivalent to $2(9p-18)$.", "####Factoring out $18$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}18p-36\\\\\\\\\n&=18\\left(\\dfrac{18p-36}{18}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=18\\left(\\dfrac{18p}{18}-\\dfrac{36}{18}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=18(p-2)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $18p-36$ is equivalent to $18(p-2)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $18p-36$:\n\n- $2(9p-18)$\n- $18(p-2)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$3(9p-12)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$9(2p-4p)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$2(9p-18)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$18(p-2)$", "correct": true}]}}}, {"item_id": "b4b7c1effc5756b89ee8f121e92ba5c1", "question_content": "**Factor $48m+42n$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $48m+42n$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $6$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48m+42n\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left(\\dfrac{48m+42n}{6}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left(\\dfrac{48m}{6}+\\dfrac{42n}{6}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=6(8m+7n)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $48m+42n$ is equivalent to $6(8m+7n)$.", "####Factoring out $3$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48m+42n\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{48m+42n}{3}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{48m}{3}+\\dfrac{42n}{3}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=3(16m+14n)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $48m+42n$ is equivalent to $3(16m+14n)$.", "####Factoring out $2$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48m+42n\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{48m+42n}{2}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=2\\left(\\dfrac{48m}{2}+\\dfrac{42n}{2}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=2(24m+21n)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $48m+42n$ is *not* equivalent to $2(12m+21n)$.", "####Factoring out $7$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}48m+42n\\\\\\\\\n&=7\\left(\\dfrac{48m+42n}{7}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=7\\left(\\dfrac{48m}{7}+\\dfrac{42n}{7}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=7\\left(\\dfrac{48}{7}m+6n\\right)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $48m+42n$ is *not* equivalent to $7(7m+6n)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $48m+42n$:\n\n- $6(8m+7n)$\n- $3(16m+14n)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$6(8m+7n)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$3(16m+14n)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$2(12m+21n)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$7(7m+6n)$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "84291c105872578f9fbd10945447494c", "question_content": "**Factor $60-36w$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $60-36w$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $6$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}60-36w\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left(\\dfrac{60-36w}{6}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=6\\left(\\dfrac{60}{6}-\\dfrac{36w}{6}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=6(10-6w)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $60-36w$ is equivalent to $6(10-6w)$.", "####Factoring out $4$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}60-36w\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{60-36w}{4}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{60}{4}-\\dfrac{36w}{4}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=4(15-9w)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $60-36w$ is *not* equivalent to $4(15-8w)$.", "####Factoring out $12$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}60-36w\\\\\\\\\n&=12\\left(\\dfrac{60-36w}{12}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=12\\left(\\dfrac{60}{12}-\\dfrac{36w}{12}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=12(5-3w)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $60-36w$ is equivalent to $12(5-3w)$.", "####Factoring out $3$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}60-36w\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{60-36w}{3}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=3\\left(\\dfrac{60}{3}-\\dfrac{36w}{3}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=3(20-12w)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $60-36w$ is *not* equivalent to $3(20+12w)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $60-36w$:\n\n- $6(10-6w)$\n- $12(5-3w)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$6(10-6w)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$4(15-8w)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$12(5-3w)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$3(20+12w)$", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "727a099e57b75fafa7f1b8ef29972194", "question_content": "**Factor $20r+60t$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $20r+60t$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $4$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}20r+60t\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{20r+60t}{4}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=4\\left(\\dfrac{20r}{4}+\\dfrac{60t}{4}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=4(5r+15t)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $20r+60t$ is equivalent to $4(5r+15t)$.", "####Factoring out $5$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}20r+60t\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\left(\\dfrac{20r+60t}{5}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\left(\\dfrac{20r}{5}+\\dfrac{60t}{5}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=5(4r+12t)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $20r+60t$ is *not* equivalent to $5(5r+12)$.", "####Factoring out $60$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}20r+60t\\\\\\\\\n&=60\\left(\\dfrac{20r+60t}{60}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=60\\left(\\dfrac{20r}{60}+\\dfrac{60t}{60}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=60\\left(\\dfrac{1}{3}r+t\\right)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $20r+60t$ is *not* equivalent to $60(20r+t)$.", "####Factoring out $20$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}20r+60t\\\\\\\\\n&=20\\left(\\dfrac{20r+60t}{20}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=20\\left(\\dfrac{20r}{20}+\\dfrac{60t}{20}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=20(r+3t)\n\\end{align}$\n\nYes, $20r+60t$ is equivalent to $20(r+3t)$.", "The following expressions are equivalent to $20r+60t$:\n\n- $4(5r+15t)$\n- $20(r+3t)$"], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "$4(5r+15t)$", "correct": true}, {"content": "$5(5r+12)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$60(20r+t)$", "correct": false}, {"content": "$20(r+3t)$", "correct": true}]}}}, {"item_id": "6f2b63bac8b05646871316e97f30b248", "question_content": "**Factor $10h+30+50j$ to identify the equivalent expressions.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": ["To factor means to rewrite an expression as a product. Let's try dividing the expression $10h+30+50j$ by each factor.", "####Factoring out $5$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}10h+30+50j\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\left(\\dfrac{10h+30+50j}{5}\\right)\\\\\\\\\n&=5\\left(\\dfrac{10h}{5}+\\dfrac{30}{5}+\\dfrac{50j}{5}\\right) \\\\\\\\\n&=5(2h+6+10j)\n\\end{align}$\n\nNo, $10h+30+50j$ is *not* equivalent to $5(2h+30+50j)$.", "####Factoring out $10$\n\n$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}10h+30+50j\\\\\\\\\n&=10\\left(\\dfrac{10h+30+50j}{10}\\right)\